						<summary>Poetical writings.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="ita"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="3r" to="81r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Miḳdash me῾at</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מקדש מעט</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/24669073">Rieti, Moses ben Isaac da, 1388-1460</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/24669073">משה בן יצחק, ראיטי‏ ‎</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Folio 2v: rhymed linesstating that the manuscript of parts I and II was given to Natan ben Binyamin (the scribe of part III) as a Purim gift by his teacher. </p>
								<p>The text seems to be incomplete. Part 1 begins on folio 4r, and part 2 on folio 27r.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. Add MS 27001.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="81v" to="87v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Igeret ya῾ar ha-Levanon</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">אגרת יער הלבנון</title>
							<note>
								<p>With several blanks left by the scribe.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/24669073" xml:lang="en">Rieti, Moses ben Isaac da, 1388-1460</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/24669073" xml:lang="he">ריאיטי, משה בן יצחק</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="88r" to="205r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Derashot ṿe-igrot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">דרשות ואגרות</title>
							<note>
								<p>Copied for the most part by Natan ben Binyamin Finzi, and including compositions of his own.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>212 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>205</height>
										<width>130</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>125/170</height>
										<width>70/100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>212 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 12 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Damp at head in part. </p>
									<p>Usage stains.</p>
									<p>Ink partly fading.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1  2" ruledLines="26 43" writtenLines="26 43">
									<p>Non-uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Pencil ruling visible in part I.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on most of the versos.</p>
									<p>Initial words in square characters.</p>
									<p>Text on folio 206-212 has been crossed out.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive and cursive scripts of the 16th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Eliyahu ben Refael ha-Rofe</name>: inscribed, folio 3r, and <name type="person" role="scribe">Natan ben Binyamin Finzi</name>: inscribed, 205v, 206r-212r.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Gio[vanni] Dom[eni]co [Carretto?]</name>, Italian censor (active 1600-1624): inscribed with his name, 1602 (folio 211v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>, and appendix § 80-84. </p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Cristoforo</name> [...]: inscribed with his name, 1592 (folio 2r).</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yehudah ben Mordekhai of Blanis</name>: inscribed, folio 3v.</p>
							<p>Folios 206r-212r contain a series of entries recording the preformance of berit milah on various occasions, and the birth of children. Some of the entires are in Italian. </p>
							<p>Folio 2r contains a list of names for kadish prayer, in Italian semi-cursive script of the 16th century.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM/BL in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Moses Rieti. Mikdash Me'at, Etc. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,012.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
